spanGrp.span: There was a bear and it called a child to play, to dance with him.
Oso kalu je t yaba ki-m jin klti ra
they there/they did not let the tiger sleep.
jie-wa t jes/ ka t nm je w kp
So they went there, where on of them found the fruit.
er wakwa mn-lo jeska maga kalw kw'-ite
and gave one to the child.
He took one and thought that the since the bear had broken the fruit open with its head, he could also do so, but his head hurt bang! And so he dropped it.
wagi t e-gla gug-w begets-ite (eh) oso t e-gla kw'u-m tsagu wa er yaba t e-gla kw'-n tsagu wa tsagu dln-s' b-ite plja
Next daddy bear ate ants and asked the child to eat them too.
er tgapa oso kaga t sawak kete-g yaba pakk-ite sawak kt
But the child would not eat them; so he dropped the stick on him bang!
Yaba ka t kete kal j-ite plja inga
But it did not reach the child.
The child bit the ants and these ran away from him.
yaba t sawak kue-g sawak k-lo-m yiga
Next, they found ripe bananas, took them along and the bear ate them;
Tgapa chomli kw'-ite chomli ts-ite chomli katw oso t
the child made a sad face, so the bear gave him a banana.
yaba w w'-g chom m'-ite e-gla
So, he gave him another one.
The child was happy and brought more down.
yaba ksen'-ka (_) chom kaj-w-m yaba t'
Then he went away dancing and grabbed the bear and went on top of him;
wagi mn klti-gate tgapa yaba gug-w mn-ga bata inga
so they danced and fell down all the way to the river bank.
Kea (_) klti-gate jan-m Jeska n mn-lo digl kga r
They swam in the river; the bear jumped onto the river, the child went away in the river;
Jeska mn-lo tsatk digl jrga Oso jk bu-m digl jrga yaba mn digl jrga
next, he went on top of the bear.
There the child talked to him.
Jeska yaba jk m'w bata inga kapag ra
Behind them came the tiger amid the branches;
Je tinga nm date buw kaljula n
so they jumed back into the river again.
er jie-wa k b-tula-m digl shg n wagweta n
